g.text: Interfacing: But not panicked. Deliberate. Focused.
Kim Kitsuragi: "A gift..." The lieutenant turns to the staircase suspiciously, looking for any signs of another presence in the shadows above.
Interfacing: You look at her rough, jagged handwriting on the note. She was in a rush, but not panicked. Deliberate. Focused.
Cuno: "A gift, huh... ?" The kid turns to the staircase. "That's fucking suspicious to Cuno."
Cuno: "A trap, probably." He nods confidently. "But don't sweat it. You got the Cuno spotting you. Let's go in."
Klaasje's Note: No response, not even an echo in the stuffy room. You notice a silk shirt on the stairs.
You: Seems she left in a hurry.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I am not drawing my gun... yet. But I don't like 'gifts'."
Klaasje's Note: "I'm sorry I fucked everyone over.
Half Light: Just don't walk into another radio trap, okay...
Volition: Relax. Not everyone is out to trap you.
Klaasje's Note: Next to stacks of bills, you see a note -- a few lines jotted down in large, uneven handwriting just as the writer was about to rush out the door.
Hand/Eye Coordination: He says he's not, but his hand moves instinctively toward his holster as he studies the note.
Klaasje's Note: The note does not reply. The jagged, rough handwriting looks like she was in a hurry.
Cuno: "Yeah-yeah." He looks around. "Fugitive on the run shit. Cuno's seen this shit before."
Klaasje's Note: "I'm sorry I fucked everyone over.
Klaasje's Note: "See you at The Return.
